The paper proposes a deep learning algorithm for tracking microtubules in time-lapse image series, which involves image segmentation, correspondence assignment, and trajectory estimation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) domains. Additionally, the proposed technique has applications in biology (cs.BIO) for characterizing the spatial arrangement of microtubules.
